rComments: One of the best professors ! She wants to see her students succeed. A lot of examples and activities to make sur that everyone understands the concepts that are being taught. If you participate and study you will do well.

Madame Dansereau is so sweet, I wish she wasnt such a hard marker lmao. I study my ass off and use Antidote a lot and it still didnt go well if you know what I mean. But shes so caring and engaging that I dont rly care lol

This was a very easy class. If you own Antidote, there's no reason you can't get an A. Most assignments and work just involves finding slang words in Canadian French. The only negative was having to have webcam on and participate in class, but she wouldn't really force you to answer if you didn't have an answer
Hard marker but for sure the best FLS Prof at Uottawa. She cares about her students and wants us to succeed. Lots of interactive activities in class. Be ready to participate! Highly recommended.

All students should take this FSL course. I learned many things about French in social contexts instead of just academic. Going to see a play in Quebec French was a great experience even though it was a bit stressful for a shy Anglo. Great FLS course and Prof Dansereau is the best!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: I had Professor Dansereau for two DLS courses this year, my two favorite courses at the university. Lots of activities and discussions in class, fair exams and final project. By far one of the best professors I've ever had. Very clear in what she expects from assignments. Also very easy to speak to outside of class. Love her!

Lectures Heavy - 3 hours. Lots of homework. She'll pick on you to answer questions. I did the mistake of not asking enough questions on the Portfolio (50%) and I did real bad. She won't give clear directions on what she wants  so ask questions!! She's not as sweet as she seems to be. I've had her for FLS courses & she's much better there. GoodLuck

Uses a lot of different activities and discussions to fill up the 3 hour lecture, it goes by surprisingly fast. Tests are easy to prepare for, based more on elaboration than memorization. She will definitely call you out though in class and ask you to answer a question.

I took this class as a helper for a class for my program. MC Dansereau is great. The only thing is that I did worse in this class than the one that it was supposed to be helping me with. But, she did encourage us to read the textbook and work hard for our grades which I appreciate. She cared about us and wanted us to succeed, which we did.

One of the best professors I've had in my undergrad! She strives to see her students succeed. She provides examples and activities to ensure that everyone understands the concepts that are being taught. Je la recommande fortement :)
La meilleure!
The best teacher I have ever taken. She was so good at what she did - and she clearly wanted us to do well. I wish she could teach me everything!

Favourite french prof ever! She is amazing, funny, and really helpful. Her marking scheme is very clear and examinations are straightforward and based off the material covered in class; no tricks at all! Make sure to attend class casue if you don't, you'll miss what is going on and will be behind on the grammar. Would recommend her to anyone:)

Mme Dansereau is the most caring prof I have ever had the good fortune to have. She cares about her subject and about your success. She offers many chances to make up and/or improve your marks, and is very generous and kind. Lectures are well-structured, exams are fair, and content is clear. Would 100% take again! You are in good hands.
Great Prof! Hard marker but definitely my fave FLS class ever. Also, she is so beautiful.

Overall a great prof! She is a tough grader and not always clear on grading criteria but shes available to answer questions outside of class. She genuinely cares about her students but make sure you come prepared to class!

Couldn't ask for a better teacher. Makes things clear and easy to understand, with lots of examples and in-class activities to clarify sometimes difficult concepts. Easily available outside of class hours. Would LOVE to have her again - couldn't have asked for a better prof!

Literally just an AMAZING professor. She is unbelievably sweet, helpful and approachable. My entire class absolutely loves her. She is so encouraging and helpful. She will do anything to make sure you do well. She's the best prof I've had in all of University. She gives me hope for the institution, to be honest! Take her class if you can!

Lots of opportunities to make up lost marks on tests. I found that the tests were a bit tough, but you should do fine if you attend class and participate, you'll be fine. A lot of case studies, but only 20$, so cheap materials. The major project was fun and the oral presentations by students supplement the readings. She is an amazing professor.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'EXTRA CREDIT']

rComments: Great fls prof. Super nice. I would  definitely take another course with her.
Bon pédagogue, bien organisée. Beaucoup de travaux , mais un bon cours.

Worst elective course I have ever taken. Prof posts her powerpoints filled with gaps so you are required to attend class. Super dry material and horrible lectures. I was under the impression that this was an into to Second Language Teaching course, but I didn't learn anything about teaching all semester. Big group projects are required, never fun!

She is the sweetest french Prof. you will ever have. She cares about her students and is effective and engaging. If you work hard, you will succeed and learn a lot.  Highly recommend taking this class!
Great prof!

Overall the class was okay. I found that a lot was attempted to be crammed in. She was helpful if you asked for it however, she makes the tests very hard choosing irregular verbs and questions that are not clear. There is also too many examples and not enough time spent on actually teaching the criteria.
Absolutely fantastic prof. So helpful.

Prof. Dansereau is the best french teacher I have ever had! Extremely nice and knowledgeable. She REALLY knows how to teach, and often focuses on real-life, day-to-day french grammar and expressions (which is super helpful!). I learnt SO MUCH in her class. For the first time, French actually makes sense and is fun!
This course is actually fun. She's a very easy marker, and as long as you try, you'll do well. She's super nice - reminds me of a kindergarten teacher. A great course overall. Highly recommend.
The cutest prof ever. She is so helpful and understanding. Very easy marker and I actually had FUN in her class :)

Elle est tellement bonne! MC est une des professeurs rares qui s'occupe vraiment de l'apprentissage de ses étudiants. Elle connait bien sa matière et elle comprend bien comment les esprits des apprenants fonctionnent... elle sait comment enseigner. Si vous voulez travailler fort afin de vous améliorer en français, prennez un de ses cours.
